Regarding VE: In my opinion the company is primarily known for what Yahoo says:
"management and operation of drinking water plants, wastewater decontamination
and recycling plants, drinking water distribution networks, and wastewater
collection networks." Perhaps not so well known, VE is "the leading private
operator of public transportation in Europe", according to the company. In the
USA, among other things, they are the SuperShuttle people.
I've held shares in an ira since '09 and also in a taxable account since '10.
Not much progress in the stock price. Which is okay with me -- given VE's size
and breadth and businesses, I can't expect great gains from rapid appreciation
of the stock. Fwiw, if anybody reading this is contemplating buying the stock,
they ought to consider if they will hold long enough to get the annual
dividend. If so, that dividend is taxed differently (a higher (!!) tax is
withheld) if the stock's in a non-taxable account, than if it's in a taxable
account. For me, I'm adding shares in my taxable account.

